---
/* Simple section focused on the core philosophy */
---

<section class="w-full py-10 md:py-32 px-6 md:px-12 bg-theme-base  transition-colors duration-500">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
    
    <span class="text-brand-gold font-sans text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-6 block font-semibold">
      Our Philosophy
    </span>
    
    <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-theme mb-12 leading-tight tracking-tight">
      Why We <span class="italic text-brand-gold opacity-90">Continue</span>
    </h2>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-10">
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <p class="font-sans text-theme-soft text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed">
          Khatam is a delicate and time-intensive craft that requires patience and precision. 
          It is part of a broader cultural heritage that is slowly disappearing as fewer people continue the practice.
        </p>

        <div class="w-16 h-[1px] bg-brand-gold/30 mx-auto"></div>

        <p class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl text-theme italic leading-snug max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          "For us, this work is not only production—it is memory, identity, and continuity."
        </p>

        <div class="w-16 h-[1px] bg-brand-gold/30 mx-auto"></div>

        <p class="font-sans text-theme-soft text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed">
          At the same time, we have seen how learning a craft can bring structure, dignity, and focus to individuals who are rebuilding their lives in a new place.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>